{"serial": "51017", "department_serial": 48, "code": "EE3038", "class": "*", "name": {"en": "Microwave Engineering", "ch": "微波工程"}, "notice": {"en": "", "ch": "建議修過「電磁學II」。"}, "instructor": {"en": ["Lin, Yo-Shen"], "ch": ["林祐生"]}, "credits": 3, "time_loc": [{"time": {"week": 3, "session": ["6"]}, "loc": {"building": "E1", "room": "019"}}, {"time": {"week": 4, "session": ["3", "4"]}, "loc": {"building": "E1", "room": "123"}}], "isRequired": false, "isFullSem": false, "MaxStu": -1, "department": {"ch": "電機工程學系", "en": "Department of Electrical Engineering"}, "system": {"ch": "學士班", "en": "Undergraduate Programme"}, "language": {"ch": "國語", "en": "Chinese"}, "card": {"ch": "不使用", "en": "None"}, "assigned": 41, "selected": 0, "remark": {"ch": "建議修過「電磁學II」。", "en": ""}, "goal": {"ch": "\"Providing a thorough physical understanding of the behaviors of circuit components and interconnections operated at microwave frequencies, and serving as a solid background for further studies on microwave and/or high-speed digital circuit designs.\"", "en": "\"Providing a thorough physical understanding of the behaviors of circuit components and interconnections operated at microwave frequencies, and serving as a solid background for further studies on microwave and/or high-speed digital circuit designs.\""}, "outline": {"ch": "\"授課內容：\nThis course is designed as an intermediate course between the undergraduate course “Electromagnetics” and the graduate course “Microwave Circuits”. It is aimed at providing a thorough physical understanding of the behaviors of circuit components and interconnections operated at microwave frequencies, and serving as a solid background for further studies on microwave or high-speed circuit designs. Topics are covered in a mostly \"\"bottom-up\"\" approach, starting from a review of the basic concept of electromagnetic theory in a more straightforward way, with emphasis on the physics behind the operation of high-frequency circuits. Followed by an introduction to microwave network theory and the design of microwave passive components. The outline of this course is as follows:\n1. Introduction to microwave engineering\n2. Impedance and electrical models\n3. The physical basis of resistance, capacitance, and inductance\n4. The physical basis of transmission line\n5. Microwave network analysis\n6. Impedance matching networks\n7. Introduction to microwave circuit designs\"", "en": "\"This course is designed as an intermediate course between the undergraduate course “Electromagnetics” and the graduate course “Microwave Circuits”. It is aimed at providing a thorough physical understanding of the behaviors of circuit components and interconnections operated at microwave frequencies, and serving as a solid background for further studies on microwave or high-speed circuit designs. Topics are covered in a mostly \"\"bottom-up\"\" approach, starting from a review of the basic concept of electromagnetic theory in a more straightforward way, with emphasis on the physics behind the operation of high-frequency circuits. Followed by an introduction to microwave network theory and the design of microwave passive components. The outline of this course is as follows:\n1. Introduction to microwave engineering\n2. Impedance and electrical models\n3. The physical basis of resistance, capacitance, and inductance\n4. The physical basis of transmission line\n5. Microwave network analysis\n6. Impedance matching networks\n7. Introduction to microwave circuit designs\""}, "textbook": {"ch": "\"教科書：\n1. Lecture notes\n2. Eric Bogatin, Signal and Power Integrity – Simplified, Prentice-Hall, 2009\n3. David M. Pozar, Microwave Engineering, 4th ed., John Wiley & Sons, Inc., 2011.\n成績計算：期中考35%，期末考35%，作業30%。\"", "en": "\"Textbook and Teaching Materials:\n1. Lecture notes\n2. Eric Bogatin, Signal and Power Integrity – Simplified, Prentice-Hall, 2009\n3. David M. Pozar, Microwave Engineering, 4th ed., John Wiley & Sons, Inc., 2011.\""}, "selfCompiledRate